    "body": "@minrk, what do you think of, when saving `foo.ipynb`:\n1. rename `foo.ipynb` -> `foo.ipynb~`\n2. write `foo.ipynb`\n3. If 2 was successful, delete `~` file.\n\nThat way, we don't litter the directory with `~` files (which I know you hate), but they are visible, obvious and easy to find in case of a problem...\n"
