    "body": "I'm the one who had the crazy out of memory / out of disk situation :).  \n\nHere's a link to how glib does safe file saves: https://developer.gnome.org/glib/stable/glib-File-Utilities.html#g-file-set-contents (it's the g_file_set_contents function)\n1. write to temp, then \n2. move to final destination\n\nSo that's one argument for @minrk 's order.\n"
